The test_files module
=====================

	>>> print test.path.name
	test_files.test

	>>> import test_files

The module provides a method which gets all possible test files
	which means *.test, *.tests, *.py
	We expect to find such extensions for test_files.*, and test_file.* here
	>>> show( test_files.get_test_scripts() )
	[...
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_file.tests'>,
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_files.tests'>,
	...
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_file.test'>,
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_files.test'>,
	...
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_file.py'>,
	 <Path '/Users/jab/.jab/python/test_files.py'>,
	...

The method can also take arguments to search directories recursively
	and args is a list of possible stems 
	>>> show( test_files.get_test_scripts(recursive=False,args=['test_files']) )
	[<Path '/.../test_files.tests'>,
	 <Path '/.../test_files.test'>,
	 <Path '/.../test_files.py'>]

